1.2 Data & Model

x <- matrix(c(.8, 102, 1, 98, .5, 100, 0.9, 105, .7, 103, 
              0.4, 110, 1.2, 99, 1.4, 87, 0.6, 113, 1.1, 89, 1.3, 93),
            nrow=11, ncol=2, byrow=T) 

#precision of measurement:
sigmaerror <- c(.03, 1)
lambdaerror <- 1/sigmaerror^2

# Pearson Correlation With Uncertainty in Measurement
mymodel <- function(){
  # Data
  for (i in 1:n){
    y[i,1:2] ~ dmnorm(mu[],TI[,])
    for (j in 1:2){
      x[i,j] ~ dnorm(y[i,j],lambdaerror[j])
    }
  }
  # Priors
  mu[1] ~ dnorm(0,.001)
  mu[2] ~ dnorm(0,.001)
  lambda[1] ~ dgamma(.001,.001)
  lambda[2] ~ dgamma(.001,.001)
  r ~ dunif(-1,1)
  # Reparameterization
  sigma[1] <- 1/sqrt(lambda[1])
  sigma[2] <- 1/sqrt(lambda[2])
  T[1,1] <- 1/lambda[1]
  T[1,2] <- r*sigma[1]*sigma[2]
  T[2,1] <- r*sigma[1]*sigma[2]
  T[2,2] <- 1/lambda[2]
  TI[1:2,1:2] <- inverse(T[1:2,1:2])
}

1.3 MCMC

samples <- jags(data = list(x = x, n = nrow(x), lambdaerror = lambdaerror),
                parameters.to.save = c("r", "mu", "sigma"),
                inits = list(list(r = 0, mu = c(0,0), lambda = c(1,1))),
                model.file = mymodel,
                n.chains = 1, n.iter = 10000, n.burnin = 1, n.thin = 1,
                jags.module = c("dic")
)

1.4 Visualization

r <- samples$BUGSoutput$sims.list$r

#Frequentist point-estimate of r:
freq.r <- cor(x[,1],x[,2])

#some plotting options to make things look better:
par(cex.main = 1.5, mar = c(5, 6, 4, 5) + 0.1, mgp = c(3.5, 1, 0), cex.lab = 1.5,
    font.lab = 2, cex.axis = 1.3, bty = "n", las=1)
# data panel:    
plot(x[,1],x[,2], type="p", pch=19, cex=1)
for (i in 1:nrow(x))
{
  lines(c(x[i,1]-sigmaerror[1],x[i,1]+sigmaerror[1]), c(x[i,2],x[i,2]))
  lines(c(x[i,1],x[i,1]), c(x[i,2]-sigmaerror[2],x[i,2]+sigmaerror[2]))
}

# correlation panel:
plot(density(r, from=-1,to=1), main="", ylab="Posterior Density", xlab="Correlation", lwd=2)
lines(c(freq.r, freq.r), c(0,100), lwd=2, lty=2)

mymodel2 <- function(){
  # Data
  for (i in 1:n){
    y[i,1:2] ~ dmnorm(mu[],TI[,])
    for (j in 1:2){
      x[i,j] ~ dnorm(y[i,j],lambdaerror[j])
    }
  }
  # Priors
  mu[1] ~ dnorm(0,.001)
  mu[2] ~ dnorm(0,.001)
  lambda[1] ~ dgamma(.001,.001)
  lambda[2] ~ dgamma(.001,.001)
  r ~ dunif(-1,1)
  lambdaerror[1] ~ dgamma(.001,.001) # 추가 
  lambdaerror[2] ~ dgamma(.001,.001) # 추가 
  # Reparameterization
  sigma[1] <- 1/sqrt(lambda[1])
  sigma[2] <- 1/sqrt(lambda[2])
  T[1,1] <- 1/lambda[1]
  T[1,2] <- r*sigma[1]*sigma[2]
  T[2,1] <- r*sigma[1]*sigma[2]
  T[2,2] <- 1/lambda[2]
  TI[1:2,1:2] <- inverse(T[1:2,1:2])
  sigmaerror[1] <- 1/sqrt(lambdaerror[1]) # 추가 
  sigmaerror[2] <- 1/sqrt(lambdaerror[2]) # 추가 
}
